---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Staff — Real Chefs. Permanently Employed. Legally Compliant."
  description="Avorix loans permanently employed chefs with an official staff leasing permit. For emergencies, seasons, or transitions — legally compliant and discreet."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-28 pb-16 px-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50/50 to-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <span class="inline-block text-brand-600 text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase mb-4">
        Module: The Reinforcement
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
        Real Chefs. Permanently Employed.<br />Legally Compliant.
      </h1>
      <div class="flex justify-center mb-6">
        <span class="inline-block bg-brand-50 border border-brand-200 text-brand-700 font-bold rounded-full px-5 py-2.5 text-sm">
          Official staff leasing permit &middot; Federal Employment Agency
        </span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        When you're short on staff, we loan you our permanently employed chefs: for emergencies, for the season, for the transition. In the hospitality industry, only a few providers hold this permit.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/en/contact"
        data-cta-location="personal-hero"
        class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors"
      >
        Book a Demo
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- When to Call -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 text-center mb-12">When to Call Us.</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 p-7">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The Emergency.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
            Your head chef is out — tomorrow is full occupancy. We send you a trained cook, by the day or by the week.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 p-7">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The Season.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
            You know in spring that you'll need two extra people in summer. Predictable, for weeks or the entire season.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 p-7">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">The Transition.</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
            Your sous chef has resigned, hiring a replacement takes time. We bridge the gap until your new hire starts.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 text-center mt-8">
        Short-notice deployments within 24 to 72 hours possible. 98 percent of requests fulfilled within 3 days.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Knowledge Stays -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">
        The Temp Chef Leaves Eventually. Their Knowledge Stays.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        Our chefs work with the Avorix Cook App and continue documenting as they go. You pay for staff and build the system in your kitchen at the same time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Legal Risk -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">
        Why "Cheap Freelancers" Can Cost You 50,000 Euros.
      </h2>
      <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-brand-500 rounded-r-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          In the hospitality industry, many businesses book "self-employed" chefs through agencies or platforms. It seems flexible and affordable. In reality, the risk of bogus self-employment lies entirely with the client — meaning you.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          During a social security audit, authorities retroactively determine whether an actual employment relationship existed. If so, you pay social security contributions, payroll tax, and late payment penalties going back years — quickly 50,000 to 100,000 euros.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          That's why we do it differently: our chefs are permanently employed by Avorix. We hold the official staff leasing permit issued by the Federal Employment Agency. This is legal, audited, and risk-free for you.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed font-bold">
          Ask every provider for this permit. Anyone who doesn't have it is not allowed to loan you staff.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Discretion -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">
        Your Guests Experience Your Kitchen. Not Ours.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        Our chefs don't wear Avorix uniforms, don't appear under our name, and are indistinguishable from your regular staff to your guests. We don't mention our clients publicly. Discretion is part of our standard.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">What Does It Cost?</h2>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border border-neutral-200 p-7">
        <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Clear hourly rates, no hidden fees. You pay for the hours booked. Travel, social security contributions, and insurance are included. No placement fee, no fine print.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/en/contact"
          data-cta-location="personal-kosten"
          class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors"
        >
          Book a Demo
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-10 text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 bg-white">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">Who are the chefs?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
            Permanently employed professionals at Avorix — with experience in upscale hotels and restaurants. Every chef is selected by us, onboarded, and works with our Cook App.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 bg-white">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">What if a chef doesn't fit our business?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
            Then we swap them out. We want the assignment to work — not just for someone to show up.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 bg-white">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">Is there a minimum booking?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed"></p>
        </details>
        <details class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 bg-white">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">How is this structured contractually?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
            Through a staff leasing agreement. This is the legally correct form when staff is loaned to another business. You receive a clean invoice; we handle all employment law matters.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 bg-white">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer">Can an assignment lead to something more?</summary>
          <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. If you'd like to hire one of our chefs permanently, let's talk. We're not a recruitment agency — but we don't block anyone either.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">
        Tell Us What Your Kitchen Needs.
      </h2>
      <a
        href="/en/contact"
        data-cta-location="personal-final"
        class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-10 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors shadow-lg shadow-brand-200"
      >
        Book a Demo
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
